<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,234,428]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,276,302]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[725,749,277,302]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles ahead of rear shield margin; opisthosoma with three ridges, middorsal ridge shorter than subdorsal ridges, ending in a broad furrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,234,428]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
This genus consists of 62 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[646,891,360,386]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[750,808,360,385]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only 3 of these have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
